<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">

<%- include('../partials/head') %>

<body>
    <%- include('../partials/navbar') %>

    <h1>Create a new post</h1>

    <form id="form-new-post" action="/images" method="post">
        <section>
            <label for="username">Enter username: </label>
            <input type="text" id="username" placeholder="Username" name="username" required>
        </section>

        <section>
            <label for="comment">Write your description here:</label> <br>                
            <textarea id="comment" cols="30" rows="5" name="description" placeholder="Description of your photo" required></textarea>
        </section>

        <section>
            <label for="url">Enter url for image: </label>
            <input type="url" id="img" placeholder="Image url" name="img" required>
        </section>
        
        <button class="button-submit">Submit</button>
    </form>

    
    <div>
        <a href="/images"><button class="button-delete">Cancel</button></a>
    </div>
    
    <h2>How do I get an image's URL?</h2>
    <p>Simply by right clicking an image from online and selecting 'Copy image address'. Alternatively, you can open the <b>image <i>(not link)</i> </b> in a new tab and grab the URL from the search bar</p>
    <%- include('../partials/footer') %>

</body>
</html>